<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04907</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT DECLARING A NATIONAL POLICY THE PROMOTION OF FINANCIAL LITERACY AS A TOOL FOR POVERTY ALLEVIATION AND NATIONAL DEVELOPMENT</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Proposes to create a Council primarily responsible in providing assistance in formulating policies
related to the promotion of financial literacy as a national concept, promoting exchange of information
on financial literacy between public and private sectors, and monitoring and evaluating financial 
literacy programs.

Intends to harness schools and workplaces as learning environments, integrating financial literacy in
anti-poverty programs, and multi-channel delivery of learning tools and information.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>NIETO, JOHN MARVIN &quot;YUL SERVO&quot; C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-09-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON POVERTY ALLEVIATION ON 2019-10-02</td></tr></table>